## Summary

**What changed:** `src/tools.rs` — `StreamingBashTool::execute` (line 474-479) and a new test (line 2041-2059).

**Two changes:**

1. **Pipefail prefix** — Every bash invocation now runs `set -o pipefail; <command>` instead of `<command>`. When a pipe member fails mid-pipeline (e.g., `rg pattern src/ | head -20` where `rg` exits 2), the non-zero exit now propagates to the tool result instead of being silently masked by the last command's exit code.

2. **Regression test** — `test_streaming_bash_pipefail_propagates_first_command_exit` verifies that `sh -c 'exit 3' | cat` returns exit code 3 (not 0), with the proper `Exit code: 3.` prefix in content.

**Verification:**
• `cargo fmt -- --check` ✅
• `cargo test streaming_bash -- --test-threads=1` — 37/37 passed ✅
• `cargo test --bin yyds -- --test-threads=1` — passed ✅
• Integration tests timed out (pre-existing, 90 tests, no bash-related ones)

